OL,3,C'I had 17 calls in one hour, it was
OL,4,Cscary': the patients without a voice
OL,6,FOlga recalled one moment where her
OL,7,Fmother was trying to ask for an oxygen
OL,8,Fmask as she was struggling to breath
OL,9,F"but the nurses thought she was
OL,10,Ffeeling scratchy so they took her for
OL,11,Fa wash and she was really mad because
OL,12,Fshe wasn't able to express herself."
OL,14,FThere was also another occasion where
OL,15,F"she (Vira) went to the GP to see if
OL,16,Fshe had a reaction on her arms from a
OL,17,Fmedication she was taking but the
OL,18,Fdoctor thought it was some sort of
OL,19,Fbacterial infection, so he prescribed
OL,20,Fanti-bacterial ointment."
