OL,3,C'I had 17 calls in one hour, it was
OL,4,Cscary': the patients without a voice
OL,6,FThe report by the Equality and Social
OL,7,FJustice Committee said mistakes and
OL,8,Fmisdiagnoses often occurred due to the
OL,9,F"wholly inappropriate use of family
OL,10,Fmembers as interpreters in medical
OL,11,Fsettings rather than trained
OL,12,Fprofessionals" and failing to provide
OL,13,Fadequate interpretation in a medical
OL,14,Fsituation was a "potential breach of
OL,15,Ftheir human rights".
OL,17,FThe committee said it is "concerned"
OL,18,Fby evidence that people from ethnic
OL,19,Fminority backgrounds continue to face
OL,20,Fworse outcomes from public sector
OL,21,Fservices in Wales.
