OL,3,C'I had 17 calls in one hour, it was
OL,4,Cscary': the patients without a voice
OL,6,FDr Shanti Karupiah, Swansea GP and
OL,7,FVice Chair Policy and Public Affairs,
OL,8,FRoyal College of GPs, told the
OL,9,FCommittee of the real-world impact of
OL,10,Flanguage barriers: "If you can't speak
OL,11,Fthe same language, it's hard to get
OL,12,Fappropriate care. If a misdiagnosis is
OL,13,Fmade, it can be the difference between
OL,14,Flife and death.
OL,16,F"I saw one middle-aged woman who had
OL,17,Fbeen coming to the practice with
OL,18,Frecurrent urinary tract infections.
OL,19,FShe came in with a relative, who was
OL,20,Fkeen to translate for us.
