OL,3,C'I had 17 calls in one hour, it was
OL,4,Cscary': the patients without a voice
OL,6,FShe added: "Language barriers have a
OL,7,Freal life impact on that individual.
OL,8,FIt's hard when you don't speak the
OL,9,Fcommon language. If English or Welsh
OL,10,Fisn't your first language, or not even
OL,11,Fyour second language, patients
OL,12,Fstruggle to be heard.
OL,14,F"It can be quite confusing and scary
OL,15,Fin the surrounding environment, in a
OL,16,Fmedical setting because they're not
OL,17,Fsure how they're going to put across
OL,18,Ftheir concerns.
