OL,3,C'I had 17 calls in one hour, it was
OL,4,Cscary': the patients without a voice
OL,6,F"The Welsh Government must recognise
OL,7,Fthat failing to provide adequate
OL,8,Finterpretation to individuals with
OL,9,Fincomplete command of either English
OL,10,For Welsh in a medical situation is a
OL,11,Fpotential breach of their human rights.
OL,13,F"The Welsh Government has set itself
OL,14,Fthe aim of an anti-racist Wales by
OL,15,F2030, a mere six years hence. That
OL,16,Frequires us to be active, not passive.
OL,17,FTo resist, rather than resign
OL,18,Fourselves to racial discrimination.
OL,19,FAnd to recognise that it is time for
OL,20,Faction, not words."
